******
[3] Vaccination of UN staff
Date: Thu 17 May 2018 10:18 AM
Source: Reuters [edited]
https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-ebola-vaccine-who/u-n-staff-on-way-to-congo-to-get-experimental-ebola-vaccine-idUSKCN1II22R


World Health Organization and other United Nations staff going to the Democratic Republic of Congo as emergency responders to an Ebola outbreak are being offered an unlicensed vaccine as protection before they go.

The WHO's deputy director-general for emergency preparedness and response Peter Salama told Reuters several staff had already signed up for immunization with the VSV-EBOV vaccine. The shot, developed by Merck, has not yet been fully licensed but has proven safe and effective in trials.

"For the 1st time, we are offering vaccination to all international responders - and we'll be doing that in Geneva and in Kinshasa," Salama said on [Thu 17 May 2018] in a telephone interview.

He said the 1st shots would be given in Geneva on [Fri 18 May 2018].

"I haven't got the latest on how many people have signed up yet, but I anticipate that a lot of people will get vaccinated."

The health ministry has said vaccinations for local health workers and contacts of people who have had Ebola can start by early next week.

[Byline: Kate Kelland]

