[5] Bordering countries: alert
Date: Fri 18 May 2018 11:31 AM
Source: Washington Post [edited]
https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/africa/who-says-ebola-outbreak-in-congo-is-not-yet-a-global-health-emergency/2018/05/18/71485152-5a1d-11e8-9889-07bcc1327f4b_story.html


A total of 11 cases of the Ebola virus were confirmed in northwest Congo on [Fri 18 May 2018], including 2 more in the bustling river port of Mbandaka, where health officials say a growing outbreak could see an "explosive increase.

The WHO has put Congo's 9 bordering countries on high alert, and the International Organization for Migration is aiding the Congolese government in deploying teams of epidemiologists and other medical staff to 16 border crossings. Both organizations are arms of the United Nations. Doctors Without Borders, known internationally by its French acronym MSF, and Alima, another nongovernmental organization, are among others leading ground efforts to contain the outbreak.

[Byline: Max Bearak]

--
